- content_for :subheader, "Nominate a Ruby Hero!"
#successbox
  %h3
    Thanks for your nomination.
#info
  %p
    Winners will be announced at
    = link_to("Railsconf", "http://en.oreilly.com/rails2011") + "."
  %p
    You can
    = link_to("nominate someone else", root_path)
#sponsormini
  :markdown  
    ### Sponsors ###
    ![O’Reilly](/images/oreilly.png)
    The Ruby Hero Awards are graciously sponsored this year by
    [O’Reilly](http://www.oreilly.com/ "O’Reilly"). O’Reilly spreads the
    knowledge of innovators through technology books, online services, and tech
    conferences (including Railsconf).
    [Railsconf](http://en.oreilly.com/rails2011 "Railsconf 2011") is taking
    place this year May 16-19 in Baltimore, Maryland, where the winners of the
    Ruby Hero Awards will be announced live on stage. [Registrations are now
    open](http://en.oreilly.com/rails2011 "Railsconf 2011") if you'd like to
    attend.
#railsbestmini
  %h4
    Looking to improve your Rails skills?
  %p
    Envy Labs recently released their first Code School course,
    #{link_to('Rails Best Practices', 'http://railsbest.com')}.
    The course is full of techniques to improve the code quality
    and maintainability of your rails apps. Available now for just $45.
    = link_to image_tag('http://railsforzombies.org/code_path_course_engine/images/promo-rbp.jpg?1300999723'), 'http://railsbest.com'
#spreadmini
  %h4
    Spread the word
  %p
    Pay it forward and 
    = link_to 'talk about us on Twitter', 'http://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=Who%20is%20your%20Ruby%20Hero?%20-%20&url=http://www.rubyheroes.com/', :title => 'Click to share this post on Twitter'
    or post a blog badge to your website to encourage others to show their gratitude.
    = image_tag "/images/banner_small.png", :alt => "Ruby Heroes"
    HTML Code: (click to copy)
    :plain
      <textarea rows="3" name="none" onclick="this.select();"><a href="http://www.rubyheroes.com" title="Ruby Hero Awards"><img alt="Ruby Hero Awards" src="http://#{request.host}/images/banner_small.png" /></a></textarea>
